This paper deals with a machine learning algorithm (Naive Bayes) for text classification, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of correlation factor, which is a statistical concept, indicating that it may also fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
